1. Create the backend folder inside our video-player-uploader
2. Inside Backend folder run npm init to initialize node modules
3. npm install cors express dotenv mongoose nodemon multer
4. We create the project structure for folders.
5. We create the index.js file - our entry file
6. We import cors for later, dotenv, app.use(express.json()) -> to parse JSON datas, and create some variables on .env file such as PORT & MONGODB_URL, than we listen and change the script in package.json to start: nodemon index.js
7. We create video Route, export it and use in our app.
8. We create the middlewares folder and create videoUpload middleware, require multer, path, and install uuid for unique video ids.
